  "prompt": "If you open a microwave oven before the beep will it release deadly microwave radiation?",
  "response": "No, opening a microwave oven before the beep will not release deadly microwave radiation. Microwave ovens are designed with safety features to prevent the leakage of microwave radiation. When you open the door, the microwave immediately stops generating microwaves, and the oven's design ensures that any residual radiation is contained within the oven's shielded compartment. \n\nThe safety standards for microwave ovens are regulated by organizations such as the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA), which ensures that the levels of microwave radiation leakage are well below harmful levels. So, it is safe to open the door at any time during operation, though it's best to wait until the cooking cycle is complete for the best cooking results.",
